Anyone else play these?<br>
<br>
And by adventure game I'm not talking Tomb Raider style games. I mean classic adventure games like the old Sierra/Lucasart games (Monkey Island, Kings Quest, Gabriel Knight etc) and more recently games like The Longest Journey, Broken Sword 1 &amp; 2 and Syberia. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=karleafv>KarleaFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 512<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/13/03 6:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1549.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Adventure games anyone?</span><hr size=1> I used to play the King's Quest series, Gabriel Knight and Maniac Mansion. My favorite of the lots was Gabriel Knight 2: The Beast Within. Dean Erikson is sooo handsome and played the role of Gabriel very well.<br>
